NEW STATEMENT:

1181
Your Honor,

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the offense of accepting a bribe. I am an individual with a clean record, aside from a single speeding ticket. To provide some context, I accepted a total of 4000 pounds in exchange for not publishing an article that revealed a company's misleading claims about their carbon emissions.

I acknowledge the seriousness of my actions, but I firmly believe that the impact of my wrongdoing was minimal. The information I possessed regarding the company's emissions was eventually disclosed by someone else just five weeks later, rendering my suppression of the article ultimately ineffectual. It is clear that my actions did not significantly contribute to any extended period of greenwashing by the company.

While I bear responsibility for my behavior, I believe it is crucial to point out certain mitigating factors. Firstly, I have no previous criminal record, which underscores the fact that my actions were out of character. Additionally, I would like to emphasize that my involvement in this offense was a direct result of being bribed and not driven by personal gain or ill intent.

Furthermore, I have reflected deeply on the consequences of my actions and have taken steps to make amends. I am committed to making compensation for the harm caused by my participation in this bribery scheme.

Your Honor, I sincerely regret my lapse in judgment and I understand the gravity of accepting a bribe. I assure you that it is a mistake I will never repeat. Throughout this process, I have experienced significant distress as a consequence of my actions, and this realization has served as a poignant lesson in the importance of upholding ethical principles.

In conclusion, I plead guilty, fully accepting the consequences of my actions. I humbly request that you take into account the mitigating factors presented, as they provide a balanced understanding of the circumstances surrounding my offense. I assure you, Your Honor, that I am committed to learning from this experience and making positive contributions to society moving forward.

Thank you for your attention.

